I was able to run the reproducer and inspect the test before the container backend stopped accepting further commands. The test is narrowly about boolean expression code generation, especially this case:

```berry
def f(i)
    var j = !i       # bug if i is erroneously modified
    return i
end
assert(f(1) == 1)
```

The relevant source search pointed to `src/be_code.c`, where unary `!` is compiled through expression-descriptor flags rather than as an ordinary value-producing operation: `NOT_MASK`, `NOT_EXPR`, `notexpr(e)`, `notmask(e)`, `jumpboolop(e,b)`, and the unary code around `notexp()` / `unaryexp()`; grep showed `src/be_code.c:584` toggling `e->not = NOT_EXPR | (e->not ^ NOT_MASK);`. This is a standard lazy boolean/jump representation, but it is unsafe if the expression descriptor still names a local variable register and later materialization stores the boolean value back into that same register. That exactly matches the test comment: compiling `var j = !i` can clobber parameter/local `i`, so `return i` returns the boolean negation result instead of the original integer.

ROOT CAUSE: `src/be_code.c:584` in the unary-not code path records `!expr` by mutating the existing `bexpdesc` (`e->not = NOT_EXPR | (e->not ^ NOT_MASK)`) without ensuring that a value-context use will materialize into a fresh/destination register rather than the operand’s register. For an operand such as local parameter `i`, the descriptor still refers to `i`’s register. When `!i` is used as a value in `var j = !i`, the delayed-not machinery can emit the boolean result into the source local’s register, clobbering `i`; boolean condition contexts are fine, but value contexts require non-destructive evaluation.

LOCAL FIX: Force delayed unary-not expressions whose operand is a local/register to be materialized into a separate register before storing/assigning, or make `notexp()` itself detach from the source register for value operands. Minimal conceptual patch:

```diff
--- a/src/be_code.c
+++ b/src/be_code.c
@@
 static void notexp(bfuncinfo *finfo, bexpdesc *e)
 {
     switch (e->type) {
     case ETBOOL:
         e->v.i = !e->v.i;
         break;
@@
     default:
         discharge(finfo, e);
+        /*
+         * Unary ! is represented lazily by e->not for jump generation.
+         * If the operand is a local/register and the expression is later
+         * needed as a value, do not let materialization reuse/clobber the
+         * operand register (e.g. "var j = !i" must not overwrite i).
+         */
+        if (e->type == ETLOCAL || e->type == ETREG) {
+            int src = e->v.idx;
+            int dst = be_code_nextreg(finfo, e);   /* fresh temporary */
+            codeABC(finfo, OP_MOVE, dst, src, 0);
+            e->type = ETREG;
+            e->v.idx = dst;
+        }
         e->not = NOT_EXPR | (e->not ^ NOT_MASK);
         break;
     }
 }
